              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Metallic sample of natural uranium discs of",
                "thickness 1mm,.4 mm and 12mm and 190 mm in diameter",
                "for transmission measurements and 1 mm thickness and",
                "160 mm in diameter for radioactive capture measurements"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight. Flight path 500m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Sectional liquid scintillation detector with",
                "volume 250. litres and cylindrical channel on axis",
                "in radiative capture measurements. Detector efficiency",
                "was constant (in 5% limits of uncertainty) in resonance",
                "energy range.",
                "That detector in transmission measurements but",
                "material with large capture cross section was",
                "introduced into axis channel instead of sample"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AREA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Area analysis with accounting of interference",
                "between resonance and potential scattering"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Flux behavior with energy was determined from",
                "thin boron counter measurements. Absolute calibration",
                "of product of neutron flux and detector efficiency",
                "was carried out by determination of resonance gap area",
                "in measurements for resonances with elastic width",
                "more less than gamma-width."
              ]
            }
          ],
